Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo, (SAN) has said professionals in politics must shun ethnic, religious and other sentiments in order to make significant impact in national development.  Speaking on Monday at the All Progressives Congress (APC) Professionals Forumâ€™s Conference, in Abuja, the Vice President stated that professionals who are politicians must stand out as people with enormous competence and used to making competence as the first means of showcasing their acumen. He noted that Public office is an instrument of service and responsibility to the people and should not be synonymous with the accumulation of power, privilege and wealth.   Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that APC national chairmanship aspirant, Senator Tanko Al-Makura said efforts would be made to make people considering politics a profession lose their job. House of Representatives Deputy Majority Whip, Honourable Nkiruka Onyejocha stressed that there would be continuous push for the inclusion of Women Professionals into Politics for good Governance.